<p>I'm using Access 2000-2003 database for C#. I like to have my <code>TypeID</code> to have a unique id as <code>CHHTP001</code>, <code>CHHTP002</code> and etc, and display the id in <code>TextBox</code> before inserting new value in the database.</p>  <pre><code>public void generateRateID() {      string id;      con.Open();      string rate = "SELECT MAX(TypeID) FROM tblRoomTypeRate";      cmd = new OleDbCommand(rate, con);      OleDbDataReader dr = cmd.ExecuteReader();      if (dr.Read())      {           id = dr[0].ToString();           id = id + 1;           txtRateID.Text = "CHHRT" + id.PadLeft(3, '0');      }      con.Close(); } </code></pre>  <p>The display in <code>TextBox</code> is <code>CHHTP001</code> at first, then <code>CHHTPCHHTP0011</code>. How can I make the <code>CHHTPCHHTP0011</code> to <code>CHHTP002</code> and so on?</p>